WEBVTT

00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:10.200
John Hazlewood: And, because Whitney, when you kind of joined,

00:00:10.200 --> 00:00:14.100
you were kind of in that… you were looking for a bootcamp type,

00:00:14.100 --> 00:00:18.300
and you had a lot of positive things to say
when you… when you joined the orientation meeting

00:00:18.300 --> 00:00:21.900
to encourage others to join.
You… and I don't…

00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:26.250
maybe you want to just tell… tell Mohamed and Mahesh kind of
what you mentioned in that meeting.

00:00:26.990 --> 00:00:30.900
Whitney McCosh: Oh, yeah, you know, I still have positive things to say,

00:00:30.900 --> 00:00:34.900
I mean, even more so now, because the experience
I'm getting here is probably

00:00:34.900 --> 00:00:38.800
really gonna help me get hired.
You know, I went from being a guy

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:42.779
who had a certificate that most employers were,

00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:46.900
willing… more than willing to ignore,
to now I have real experience

00:00:46.900 --> 00:00:51.300
at a tech company, working with their data stack,

00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:54.900
and, you know, running SQL queries,
building data pipelines.

00:00:54.900 --> 00:00:58.069
I mean, that looks,

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:02.300
so much better on your certificate
than just,

00:01:02.300 --> 00:01:06.370
"I took a 4-week course in Excel."
And so,

00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:11.000
So, so yeah, my prospects have really,
have really increased.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:14.600
And, and you know,
I always did well in school,

00:01:14.600 --> 00:01:18.420
but, like, now I'm in a position in life
where I'm kind of...

00:01:19.390 --> 00:01:22.170
I need a career shift,
you know, I need,

00:01:23.180 --> 00:01:26.430
to get into tech.
I'm juggling a bunch of,

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:30.500
Of jobs which are fun,
but kind of low-paying,

00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.419
trying to make ends meet,
and this,

00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:37.300
this experience could really change my life,

00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:41.200
and I want to share that
with anyone else who's interested in the opportunity.

00:01:41.200 --> 00:01:45.930
When you look at something like Bootcamp University,
these places, they cost thousands of dollars.

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:49.700
The ones that make guarantees of job offers.

00:01:49.700 --> 00:01:54.000
after completion, don't deliver on those promises,
for various reasons.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:58.500
They disqualify internships,
or if the candidate doesn't want to move to a new city,

00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:02.300
they say that he's not seeking a job,
so it doesn't count,

00:02:02.300 --> 00:02:04.900
and they make all kinds of excuses
to not actually make a difference in the life of the student while they're charging

00:02:04.900 --> 00:02:09.000
you know, exponentially more money than we are,
and so, so yeah,

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:12.300
I would definitely encourage anyone
thinking about joining us

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:15.500
to go ahead and give it a try.
You won't regret it.
